supportDesc.extent: ii, 73, ii leaves + 5 leaves : 244 x 158 (170 x 90) mm, bound to 250 x 160 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Some diagrams and tables in red and black.

binding.p: Modern cardboard quarter covers with red patterned sides and brown leather corners and spine.

origin.p: The copy is undated, perhaps produced in India in the 19th century.

provenance: Formerly owned by George A. Plimpton (bookplate inside front cover).
